CS||cp||FP||AT|^B@2^Y@3Chapter VIII of Part II included a discussion of the no-trump echo in which a Defender, in following suit with his low cards, gives his Partner a count on the suit by echoing (playing high-low) to show only two. This often enables Partner to know just how long to hold up a high card in the suit to destroy Declarer’s communications. The negative inference was also explained. Failure to echo would show three or more low cards in the suit.|
